<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1536" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1536">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/44.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">French Chargé
                                        d’Affaires</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-18">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 18, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                                receipt, in due course, of the Ambassador’s note of the 20th ultimo,
                                with which was enclosed a copy of a communication addressed to him
                                by two French priests and a Spanish priest, giving an account of the
                                treatment accorded to them by the Mexican authorities at Saltillo
                                and furnishing much information as to general conditions in
                                Mexico.</p>
                            <p>The Department is extremely grateful to the Ambassador for having
                                furnished it with this information.</p>
                            <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>